This paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a multitask approach based on a recurrent neural network, which involves machine learning techniques and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with social media analysis, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
